programme.desc: Its time for baby woolly monkey Julio to leave his life living with humans, and theres a shocking exit from the park for a capuchin monkey family when, 18 months after their rescue, a court order means they have to leave.

programme.title: Rewilding
programme.desc: Andalusia is a mosaic of extreme habitats. Over the course of history, human settling and hunting had a fundamental impact on these landscapes and their fauna.

programme.title: Pride Rules
programme.desc: Say hello to a season of plenty as flood waters recede and vast herds of prey return to the Chobes banks. Watch Keeza and her cub make a break for it.

programme.title: Africas Hunters
programme.desc: Theres a new face in a family of spotted hyenas. Spotty is a princess, the daughter of an alpha female, and destined to be leader of the Chimbwe Clan that live in the heart of Zambias Luangwa Valley.

programme.title: Hope for Wildlife
programme.sub-title: A Raccoon, A Ring and Four Rescues
programme.desc: When a tiny piece of trash ruins a racoons life, Dr Jessica cuts it free. However, Hope has to face tough decisions about its future.

programme.title: Malawi Wildlife Rescue
programme.desc: The team face a tough decision when Estis leg infection slows a young duikers release. They track and collar a young lion with DrAmanda, check on an ailing bush baby, and greet a noisy new addition to the centre: a grumpy grey parrot.

programme.title: Ol Pejeta Diaries
programme.desc: A baby rhinos mother is illegally shot and Ol Pej staff have to calm the wild baby. Its not ideal to separate the calf from her mother, but the situation is dire, and the calf will have to be hand-raised.

programme.title: Ol Pejeta Diaries
programme.desc: Kenyas largest and busiest private game reserve including some of Africas rarest and most endangered species.
